        "contenuto_esteso": "To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. Lebanon: Israeli army tells residents Tyre to evacuate, more and more people displaced Middle East Issued on: 07/03/2026 - 14:54 Over the past week, Israel has issued evacuation warnings before launching heavy strikes on southern Lebanon and the southern suburbs of Beirut. The IDF estimates that more than 300,000 Lebanese civilians have so far evacuated their villages in southern Lebanon.UN Human Rights spokesperson Thameen Al-Kheetan provides further details on human rights violations since the start of the conflict. Sanaa's mass rally amid regional strikes: Houthis warn of escalation after death of Khamenei 07/03/2026 Middle East Israel continues to strike Lebanon: At least 16 killed in raids on Nabi Chit 07/03/2026 Middle East Air raid sirens sound, blasts heard in Jerusalem 07/03/2026 Middle East Humanitarian crisis looming: 300,000 displaced as Israeli army pounds Lebanon 07/03/2026 Middle East Israel strikes eastern Lebanese town: At least 16 killed in raids on Nabi Chit 07/03/2026 Lebanon Millions of workers facing uncertainty as tensions escalate in the Middle East 07/03/2026 Middle East Russia sharing intelligence information to help Tehran, officials say 07/03/2026 Middle East Israel raids deep into Lebanon: Israeli troops engage Hezbollah after helicopter raid 07/03/2026 Middle East Kurdish Iraq draws a line: Erbil warns against attacks on Iran from Kurdish territory 07/03/2026 Middle East"
